articles.description: Israel's military said on Thursday it had struck hundreds of Hezbollah rocket launchers that had been targeted at Israel.
articles.title: UN peacekeepers in Lebanon urge de-escalation after heavy airstrikes

articles.description: Israeli forces killed at least 14 Palestinians in tank and air strikes on north and central areas of the Gaza Strip on Friday, medics said, as tanks advanced further into northwest Rafah near the border with Egypt.
articles.title: Israeli forces deepen raid in Rafah, kill 14 people across Gaza

articles.title: Deadly floods add to fiscal strains in central Europe

articles.description: She speaks seven languages, has a PhD in particle physics, an apartment in Budapest plastered with her own pastel drawings of nudes, and a career that took her around Africa and Europe doing humanitarian work.
articles.title: On the trail of the mystery woman whose company licensed exploding pagers

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: About 10 senior Hezbollah commanders were killed along with Ibrahim Aqil, leader of the movement's Radwan special forces unit who was attacked in an Israeli air strike in Beirut on Friday, Israel's military spokesperson said.
articles.title: Israeli military says around 10 senior Hezbollah commanders killed along with Aqil

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Ibrahim Aqil, the Hezbollah operations commander killed in an Israeli strike on Friday, had a $7 million bounty on his head for two 1983 Beirut truck bombings that killed more than 300 people at the American embassy and a U.S. Marines barracks.
articles.title: Killed Hezbollah commander Aqil was wanted for deadly 1983 US embassy, Marine blasts

articles.author: Corina Pons
articles.description: Edmundo Gonzalez told Reuters he could have been jailed and possibly tortured had he stayed in Venezuela.
articles.title: Exclusive: Venezuela's exiled opposition head was warned: 'they're coming for you'

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Serbia's government ministers on Friday agreed to reintroduce compulsory military service which was abolished 14 years ago, President Aleksandar Vucic said, praising the decision as an important step to improve the country's defence readiness.
articles.title: Serbia moves to reintroduce compulsory military service

articles.author: Andrew Gray
articles.description: Kosovo Prime Minister Albin Kurti on Friday accused Western officials of "appeasement" towards Serbia, driven by what he said were overblown fears that Belgrade would move closer to Moscow.
articles.title: Kosovo PM Kurti accuses West of 'appeasement' towards Serbia over Russia fears

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Thirty-four Tunisian lawmakers proposed on Friday an urgent bill to strip the administrative court of its authority to adjudicate electoral disputes, a move that the opposition says would discredit an Oct. 6 presidential election.
articles.title: Tunisia lawmakers propose stripping court of election oversight ahead of vote
